    {
      "id": "fbcdc244_4dfc0db8",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/contrib/external-schema-repo-generator/environment.config",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 10,
      "message": "Bartek,\n\nWell, the whole intention of this script is to reach out to 3GPP repos, which contain openAPI descriptions, download them and prepare a configMap, which can be used with any ONAP component (we`re mainly targeting DCAE components at this moment), which uses these openAPIs.\nThe whole intention of that script is to reach out to the repo, and generate the configMap.\n\nI totally understand the principles of \"Internet independence\" for ONAP, and we`ve been fighting with it quite a long time too. I fully support this initiative for run-time stuff.\n\nNow, the script, which we`re trying to get to OOM/contrib is meant to be executed manually, by a human operator, and perhaps not necessarily from the ONAP installation. I don`t think, this is run-time operations.\n\nThere is another script, which is assigning the generated configMap to the ONAP component K8S deployment spec. This one shall be used in ONAP run-time environment, but it has no internet dependency... and that one is a run-time script.\n\nWe intentionally separated these two scripts exactly to deal with run-time internet independency 😊 It is meant to be used by the system operator, and not by the ONAP itself.\n\nPerhaps OOM/contrib is not the right place to store such a script.\nIn this context would You be able to recommend another place, where it could be stored and exposed for use?\n\nRgds,\nDamian",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5597,
        "name": "Damian Nowak",
        "display_name": "Damian Nowak",
        "email": "damian.nowak@nokia.com",
        "username": "deen1985"
      },
      "updated": "2020-10-09 07:34:29.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "e9c9244c_4c5db6e6",
      "unresolved": true
    },
